WEBVTT

00:01.768 --> 00:03.236
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

00:03.236 --> 00:05.138
MY SON DID HIT SOMEONE.

00:05.138 --> 00:07.974
<i>HE DID NOT HIT LIZZIE.</i>
<i>HE DID NOT HIT BENNY YOUNG.</i>

00:07.974 --> 00:10.210
LYING.
<i>THERE'S THE CAR.</i>

00:10.210 --> 00:11.411
<i>HERE IS THE VICTIM.</i>

00:11.411 --> 00:12.746
YOU'RE A CLEVER BASTARD.

00:12.746 --> 00:14.247
D.A. WOULD LIKE TO DISCUSS
A DEAL.

00:14.247 --> 00:15.281
David: EXCELLENT.

00:15.281 --> 00:16.416
YOU GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

00:16.416 --> 00:17.951
[ SCREAMS ]

00:17.951 --> 00:20.787
NINE?
NINE IS NO LONGER A PROBLEM.

00:20.787 --> 00:22.756
PRETTY SURE
HE'S GONNA KILL YOU.

00:22.756 --> 00:23.890
I'M NOT SCARED OF HIM.

00:23.890 --> 00:24.891
YOU SHOULD BE.

00:24.891 --> 00:25.959
Tony: BECAUSE
I'VE GOT A COURT ORDER

00:25.959 --> 00:27.393
TO HAVE HIM TAKEN
OFF LIFE SUPPORT.

00:27.393 --> 00:29.329
I DON'T WANT THIS CLOWN
TALKING ABOUT MY MAMA.

00:29.329 --> 00:30.430
OH, BENNY!

00:34.635 --> 00:36.269
BENNY?

00:36.269 --> 00:37.671
BENNY!
WHAT?

00:37.671 --> 00:38.639
BENNY!

00:38.639 --> 00:39.606
NURSE!

00:39.606 --> 00:41.007
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

00:41.007 --> 00:41.975
HE'S AWAKE.

00:41.975 --> 00:43.309
HE'S AWAKE!

00:43.309 --> 00:45.512
I'LL CALL THE DOCTOR.

00:45.512 --> 00:47.113
DARLENE,
COME WITH ME.

00:47.113 --> 00:49.182
OKAY.

00:49.182 --> 00:50.851
SAY SOMETHING ELSE, BABY.

00:50.851 --> 00:53.119
SAY SOMETHING ELSE.
I HEARD YOU.

00:53.119 --> 00:56.957
BENNY,
HOW ARE YOU, BABY?

00:56.957 --> 00:59.425
I GOT A HEADACHE.

00:59.425 --> 01:01.568
YEAH, YEAH,
I'LL BET YOU DO.

01:03.604 --> 01:06.406
WHERE AM I?

01:06.406 --> 01:09.008
YOU'RE IN THE HOSPITAL,
BABY.

01:09.008 --> 01:10.310
WHAT HAPPENED?

01:10.310 --> 01:14.548
YOU WERE IN AN ACCIDENT.

01:14.548 --> 01:15.916
[ SIGHS ]

01:15.916 --> 01:18.284
MY TRUCK ALL RIGHT?

01:18.284 --> 01:19.152
HMM?

01:19.152 --> 01:21.822
IS MY TRUCK ALL RIGHT?

01:21.822 --> 01:22.789
YEAH.

01:22.789 --> 01:24.457
WHERE IS IT?

01:24.457 --> 01:27.360
BOY, DON'T YOU WORRY
ABOUT THAT TRUCK RIGHT NOW.

01:27.360 --> 01:30.096
MY THROAT HURTS.

01:30.096 --> 01:32.498
YEAH, BABY,
I BET IT DOES.

01:32.498 --> 01:35.368
YOU HAD A TUBE
DOWN YOUR THROAT.

01:40.206 --> 01:41.808
IS THAT MR. WATSON?

01:41.808 --> 01:43.877
YEAH.

01:43.877 --> 01:46.513
HOW YOU DOIN', BENNY?

01:46.513 --> 01:47.914
[ SIGHS ]

01:47.914 --> 01:49.850
IT'S TOO BRIGHT IN HERE.

01:49.850 --> 01:51.652
I WANT TO GO TO SLEEP.

01:51.652 --> 01:54.187
YEAH, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT A MINUTE.

01:54.187 --> 01:56.156
I WANT YOU TO TALK
TO THE DOCTOR FIRST, OKAY?

01:56.156 --> 01:57.958
IT'S TOO BRIGHT IN HERE.
JUST WAIT.

02:01.835 --> 02:05.238
MR. YOUNG?

02:05.238 --> 02:06.840
YEAH.

02:06.840 --> 02:08.775
I'M DR. BAILER.

02:08.775 --> 02:11.778
DO YOU KNOW WHERE YOU ARE?

02:11.778 --> 02:14.948
IN THE HOSPITAL.

02:14.948 --> 02:16.049
THAT'S RIGHT.

02:16.049 --> 02:18.251
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT DAY IT IS?

02:20.286 --> 02:21.655
IT'S THURSDAY.

02:23.957 --> 02:26.426
ACTUALLY, SATURDAY.

02:26.426 --> 02:30.063
OKAY.

02:30.063 --> 02:31.998
DOES ANYTHING HURT?

02:34.034 --> 02:36.537
MY HEAD.

02:36.537 --> 02:40.507
YEAH, WELL,
YOU HIT IT PRETTY HARD.

02:42.543 --> 02:44.811
WHERE'S THAT GIRL AT?

02:44.811 --> 02:46.479
WHAT GIRL?

02:46.479 --> 02:49.950
THE ONE
THAT WAS BY MY BED CRYING.

02:49.950 --> 02:52.553
WHAT GIRL, BABY?

02:52.553 --> 02:53.820
[ SIGHS ]

02:53.820 --> 02:55.455
THE CUTE ONE.

02:55.455 --> 02:59.826
SOMETIMES CONFUSION
WILL SET IN ABOUT THIS TIME.

02:59.826 --> 03:01.768
YEAH, I AIN'T CONFUSED.

03:01.768 --> 03:05.939
SHE SMELLED GOOD.

03:05.939 --> 03:08.141
I DON'T THINK
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

03:08.141 --> 03:11.912
THE DAMN GIRL IN THE PURPLE.

03:11.912 --> 03:14.414
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

03:14.414 --> 03:16.617
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO GET AGITATED.

03:16.617 --> 03:19.986
THIS IS ALSO A SYMPTOM OF
WHEN YOU'RE OUT FOR TOO LONG.

03:19.986 --> 03:21.788
[ SIGHS ]

03:21.788 --> 03:24.257
IN THE PURPLE.

03:24.257 --> 03:25.792
YOU MEAN DARLENE?

03:25.792 --> 03:26.927
MM, PRETTY GIRL.

03:26.927 --> 03:28.128
MM‐HMM.

03:28.128 --> 03:31.732
SHE WAS HOLDING MY HAND
AND RUBBING MY HEAD

03:31.732 --> 03:32.966
AND ALL THAT.

03:32.966 --> 03:35.201
WHEN DID SHE DO THIS,
MR. YOUNG?

03:35.201 --> 03:37.170
[ GRUNTS ]

03:37.170 --> 03:39.840
SHE ‐‐ SHE WAS HERE TODAY.

03:39.840 --> 03:41.307
SHE WAS HERE?

03:41.307 --> 03:42.876
I AIN'T CRAZY.

03:42.876 --> 03:43.877
I KNOW.

03:43.877 --> 03:46.647
I DON'T KNOW
HOW HE WOULD KNOW THIS.

03:46.647 --> 03:48.549
I WAS UP.

03:48.549 --> 03:50.450
YOU WERE?

03:50.450 --> 03:51.552
MM‐HMM.

03:51.552 --> 03:55.321
YEAH, I'VE BEEN WAKING UP,
BUT JUST ‐‐

03:55.321 --> 03:57.858
I CAN'T KEEP MY EYES OPEN.

03:57.858 --> 03:59.993
YOU'VE BEEN WAKING UP?

03:59.993 --> 04:02.836
YEAH.

04:02.836 --> 04:05.305
I HEARD YOU CRYING.

04:05.305 --> 04:06.306
OH.

04:06.306 --> 04:07.574
AND SPITTING.

04:07.574 --> 04:08.642
[ LAUGHS ]

04:08.642 --> 04:10.010
SPITTING?

04:10.010 --> 04:12.946
MM‐HMM,
PRAY SPITTING ALL OVER ME.

04:12.946 --> 04:14.781
I SMELT THE OLIVE OIL.

04:14.781 --> 04:15.816
[ SNIFFS ]

04:15.816 --> 04:17.851
HOLY OIL.

04:17.851 --> 04:20.721
WELL, YEAH, I DID DO THAT.

04:20.721 --> 04:22.222
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:22.222 --> 04:25.058
THAT HOLY OIL HAD ME ABOUT TO
SLIDE RIGHT UP OUT OF THIS BED.

04:25.058 --> 04:27.894
[ LAUGHS ]

04:27.894 --> 04:30.897
‐‐Captions by VITAC‐‐
www.vitac.com

04:30.897 --> 04:33.933
CAPTIONS PAID FOR BY
DISCOVERY COMMUNICATIONS

04:38.171 --> 04:39.773
BRING THAT GIRL BACK IN HERE

04:39.773 --> 04:41.908
TO KEEP SINGING TO ME
LIKE SHE WAS.

04:41.908 --> 04:44.110
SHE SUNG TO YOU?

04:44.110 --> 04:45.178
YEAH.

04:45.178 --> 04:46.780
[ GRUNTS ]

04:46.780 --> 04:48.381
I'M TIRED.

04:50.416 --> 04:52.218
DOC, TURN THAT DAMN LIGHT OFF.

04:54.621 --> 04:57.290
NOW STOP CRYING.
YOU'RE SNOTTING ON ME.

04:57.290 --> 04:59.626
[ LAUGHS ]

04:59.626 --> 05:01.367
WHERE'S CANDACE AT?

05:01.367 --> 05:02.769
WHO'S CANDACE?

05:02.769 --> 05:03.937
HIS SISTER.

05:03.937 --> 05:05.405
WHERE'S SHE AT?

05:05.405 --> 05:07.340
SHE'S NOT HERE, BABY.

05:10.611 --> 05:12.412
YOU TOLD HER I WAS HERE?

05:12.412 --> 05:14.915
SHE KNEW.

05:14.915 --> 05:17.884
HOW LONG I BEEN OUT FOR?

05:17.884 --> 05:20.120
YOU'VE BEEN OUT
FOR A WEEK, BABY.

05:20.120 --> 05:22.055
OH, YOU GOT TO CALL HER.

05:22.055 --> 05:24.290
I WILL.

05:24.290 --> 05:26.727
[ SIGHS ]
I WANT TO SEE HER.

05:26.727 --> 05:28.662
OKAY.

05:28.662 --> 05:30.063
I'M TIRED.

05:30.063 --> 05:32.198
I WANT TO GO TO SLEEP.

05:32.198 --> 05:33.767
IS THIS NORMAL?

05:33.767 --> 05:35.401
IT'S THE MEDS.

05:35.401 --> 05:36.970
CALL CANDACE.

05:36.970 --> 05:38.872
OKAY, I WILL.

05:38.872 --> 05:40.373
[ SIGHS ]

05:42.609 --> 05:44.210
[ SIGHS ]

05:44.210 --> 05:45.946
MR. YOUNG.

05:45.946 --> 05:47.981
DAMN, MAN.

05:47.981 --> 05:50.150
I'M SORRY,
BUT BEFORE YOU GO TO SLEEP,

05:50.150 --> 05:53.419
I'D LIKE YOU
TO LIFT YOUR LEFT HAND.

05:55.455 --> 05:58.592
CAN I SLAP YOU
ACROSS THE FACE WITH IT?

05:58.592 --> 05:59.693
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:59.693 --> 06:00.967
SURE.

06:00.967 --> 06:02.736
[ SIGHS ]

06:02.736 --> 06:06.640
AND THIS IS MY RIGHT HAND.

06:06.640 --> 06:08.141
SEE IT?

06:08.141 --> 06:09.610
NOW YOUR FEET.

06:09.610 --> 06:12.646
YOU WANT ME TO DO THE DAMN
HOKEY POKEY FOR YOU TOO, MAN?

06:12.646 --> 06:14.347
BENNY, COME ON NOW.

06:14.347 --> 06:17.150
I'M SORRY, MOM.
I'M TIRED.

06:17.150 --> 06:19.586
NOW YOU CAN GO TO SLEEP.

06:19.586 --> 06:21.387
REST.

06:21.387 --> 06:23.356
WOW.

06:23.356 --> 06:25.726
WHAT?

06:25.726 --> 06:29.229
I'VE HEARD ABOUT MIRACLES.

06:29.229 --> 06:31.164
THIS IS ONE.

06:31.164 --> 06:34.234
THAT'S MY GOD.

06:34.234 --> 06:37.971
MY GOD! [ LAUGHS ]

06:37.971 --> 06:39.873
YOUR GOD WANTS ME
TO GET SOME SLEEP.

06:39.873 --> 06:41.508
GET OFF ME
AND LEAVE ME ALONE.

06:41.508 --> 06:43.376
[ LAUGHS ]

06:43.376 --> 06:45.145
LOVE YOU.

06:45.145 --> 06:47.548
LOVE YOU, TOO.

06:51.251 --> 06:53.019
GOOD MORNING.

06:53.019 --> 06:54.888
WHERE'S WYATT?

06:54.888 --> 06:56.422
I'M GOOD, THANK YOU.
HOW ARE YOU?

06:56.422 --> 06:57.323
OH, DAMN IT, CELINE.

06:57.323 --> 06:58.759
WHERE IS WYATT?

06:58.759 --> 07:01.001
HE'S ON THE LANAI.

07:01.001 --> 07:02.769
THANK YOU.

07:02.769 --> 07:05.038
AND MR. CRYER?

07:05.038 --> 07:06.206
WHAT?

07:06.206 --> 07:08.575
I LOVE THE WAY YOU...

07:08.575 --> 07:12.212
TOOK CONTROL
AND PROTECTED HIM.

07:12.212 --> 07:14.981
I WISH YOU WERE THAT WAY
WITH ALL YOUR CHILDREN.

07:25.692 --> 07:27.728
WYATT.

07:27.728 --> 07:28.795
YEAH.

07:28.795 --> 07:31.632
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
OUT HERE, SON?

07:31.632 --> 07:35.135
I'M JUST THINKING.

07:35.135 --> 07:38.271
JUST THINKING ABOUT WHAT?

07:40.306 --> 07:43.376
LIFE.

07:45.411 --> 07:49.683
LIFE'S A BITCH, WYATT.

07:51.918 --> 07:53.787
I NEED YOU TO BELIEVE

07:53.787 --> 07:57.123
THAT YOU CAN HOLD
THIS TOGETHER, OKAY?

07:57.123 --> 07:58.592
OKAY.

07:58.592 --> 08:01.401
YOU CAN DO IT.

08:01.401 --> 08:04.304
LISTEN...

08:04.304 --> 08:08.141
I'M GONNA GO TO WORK,
BUT I'LL BE BACK FOR LUNCH.

08:08.141 --> 08:10.577
WE CAN TALK MORE
THEN, OKAY?

08:10.577 --> 08:12.646
ALL RIGHT.

08:12.646 --> 08:13.814
THERE YOU ARE.

08:13.814 --> 08:16.517
I'VE BEEN LOOKING ALL OVER
FOR YOU.

08:16.517 --> 08:18.484
KEEP ON HIM,
WOULD YOU?

08:18.484 --> 08:19.452
I WILL.

08:21.487 --> 08:23.757
SEE YOU LATER, SON.

08:23.757 --> 08:25.491
SEE YOU, DAD.

08:27.293 --> 08:28.529
GOOD MORNING.

08:28.529 --> 08:31.364
GOOD MORNING.

08:31.364 --> 08:34.034
ARE YOU OKAY?

08:34.034 --> 08:37.871
YEAH.

08:37.871 --> 08:40.073
WHY DON'T YOU COME IN,
HAVE SOME BREAKFAST?

08:40.073 --> 08:41.441
NO, I'M NOT HUNGRY.

08:41.441 --> 08:43.710
WELL, I COULD HAVE CELINE
BRING SOMETHING OUT TO YOU.

08:43.710 --> 08:46.680
MOM, I'M NOT HUNGRY.

08:51.484 --> 08:54.120
WYATT...

08:54.120 --> 08:56.990
I KNOW THIS HAS BEEN HARD
ON YOU.

08:59.025 --> 09:01.668
HARD ON <i>ME?</i>

09:01.668 --> 09:03.904
MOM, A LITTLE GIRL IS DEAD,

09:03.904 --> 09:06.472
AND HANNA'S SON
IS IN THE HOSPITAL.

09:08.509 --> 09:09.976
I KNOW.

09:13.013 --> 09:16.082
YOU DESERVE
TO BE HERE WITH US.

09:16.082 --> 09:19.820
YOU MADE A MISTAKE, WYATT,

09:19.820 --> 09:22.689
A TERRIBLE MISTAKE,

09:22.689 --> 09:25.391
BUT THERE'S NOTHING YOU CAN DO
ABOUT IT NOW.

09:25.391 --> 09:26.459
DO YOU HEAR ME?

09:28.494 --> 09:32.866
MOM, I FEEL SO BAD.

09:32.866 --> 09:35.101
I KNOW.

09:35.101 --> 09:38.605
I KNOW, HONEY.

09:38.605 --> 09:43.043
BUT I PROMISE YOU,
IT'LL ALL BE OVER IN TIME.

09:45.746 --> 09:49.850
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

09:49.850 --> 09:51.351
YOU WILL.

09:54.487 --> 09:56.990
YOU WILL.

09:56.990 --> 09:58.458
COME ON.

09:58.458 --> 10:00.393
COME INSIDE.

10:00.393 --> 10:03.236
I'LL BE IN
IN A MINUTE.

10:03.236 --> 10:05.572
I JUST NEED SOME AIR.

10:05.572 --> 10:07.741
I'VE BEEN LOCKED UP
IN THAT PLACE.

10:07.741 --> 10:09.743
OKAY.

10:09.743 --> 10:12.613
I JUST WANT
SOME FRESH AIR, OKAY?

10:40.541 --> 10:41.742
[ DOORBELL BUZZES ]

10:41.742 --> 10:43.510
HEY, THERE,
CAN I HELP YOU?

10:43.510 --> 10:45.478
[ BUZZING CONTINUES ]

10:48.248 --> 10:50.050
LOOKING FOR MY DAUGHTER.

10:50.050 --> 10:51.918
OKAY, UH,
WHO'S YOUR DAUGHTER?

10:51.918 --> 10:54.054
AMANDA CRYER.

10:54.054 --> 10:55.055
OH, YEAH.

10:55.055 --> 10:58.191
OH, AMANDA LEFT HERE
EARLY THIS MORNING.

10:58.191 --> 10:59.826
YOU KNOW WHERE SHE WENT?

10:59.826 --> 11:02.368
[ CHUCKLES ]
NAH, THESE YOUNG GIRLS,

11:02.368 --> 11:04.538
THEY DON'T TELL ME
WHERE THEY'RE GOING.

11:04.538 --> 11:07.007
HM. ABOUT WHAT TIME
DOES SHE GET BACK USUALLY?

11:07.007 --> 11:09.242
SHE'S BACK 3:00,
USUALLY.

11:11.277 --> 11:14.147
I THINK I'LL TRY TO TALK TO HER
AT SCHOOL.

11:14.147 --> 11:16.416
I DON'T THINK YOU'LL FIND HER
AT SCHOOL.

11:16.416 --> 11:17.350
WHY NOT?

11:17.350 --> 11:19.252
WELL, I HEAR SHE QUIT.

11:19.252 --> 11:20.721
SHE WHAT?

11:20.721 --> 11:21.788
QUIT.

11:21.788 --> 11:23.056
SCHOOL?

11:23.056 --> 11:24.324
YEAH.

11:24.324 --> 11:25.559
AND HOW WOULD YOU
KNOW THAT?

11:25.559 --> 11:28.829
SMALL BUILDING,
A LOT OF COLLEGE KIDS.

11:28.829 --> 11:30.396
WORD GETS AROUND.

11:39.039 --> 11:40.707
[ CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

11:40.707 --> 11:42.208
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

12:03.637 --> 12:05.906
THE EARLY BIRD
BRINGS THE BAGELS.

12:05.906 --> 12:07.240
PARDON?

12:07.240 --> 12:08.875
I GOT 'EM.

12:08.875 --> 12:09.976
AND A COFFEE FOR YOU.

12:09.976 --> 12:11.612
AH, THANK YOU.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

12:11.612 --> 12:13.379
LANDON?
YES, SIR.

12:13.379 --> 12:14.881
UM...

12:14.881 --> 12:18.585
WHAT'S YOUR LIFE LIKE?

12:18.585 --> 12:20.787
EXCUSE ME?

12:20.787 --> 12:22.222
I MEAN, BEING GAY,

12:22.222 --> 12:24.858
IF ‐‐ IF YOU DON'T MIND
MY ASKING.

12:24.858 --> 12:29.229
MY LIFE IS JUST LIKE YOURS.

12:29.229 --> 12:32.899
YES, I‐I MEAN...

12:32.899 --> 12:36.903
HAS IT BEEN HARD DEALING
WITH DISCRIMINATION?

12:36.903 --> 12:38.071
YES.

12:38.071 --> 12:40.607
HOW DO YOU DEAL
WITH THAT?

12:40.607 --> 12:44.811
HOW DID WE ALL DEAL WITH IT,
BEING BLACK AND ALL?

12:44.811 --> 12:46.813
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:46.813 --> 12:47.781
YES.

12:47.781 --> 12:51.552
I'M SORRY.
IT'S A FOOLISH QUESTION.

12:51.552 --> 12:54.120
IS THERE A REASON
WHY YOU ASKED?

12:56.156 --> 12:57.390
NO.

12:57.390 --> 13:02.335
NO, JUST ‐‐ JUST WONDERING.

13:02.335 --> 13:03.670
OKAY, ANYTIME.

13:03.670 --> 13:06.006
[ CHUCKLES ]
MY, OH, MY.

13:06.006 --> 13:07.641
YOU'RE HERE EARLY.

13:07.641 --> 13:09.409
I'M SURPRISED
TO SEE YOU HERE.

13:09.409 --> 13:11.211
WELL, I NEEDED TO STOP BY
AND TALK TO AMANDA.

13:11.211 --> 13:12.312
I WENT TO HER APARTMENT
ON THE WAY.

13:12.312 --> 13:13.346
HOW'S SHE DOING?

13:13.346 --> 13:15.348
I HAVE NO IDEA.
SHE WASN'T THERE.

13:15.348 --> 13:17.518
WE HAVEN'T SPOKEN IN DAYS.

13:17.518 --> 13:18.585
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:18.585 --> 13:20.987
I DON'T KNOW, DAVID,
BUT I'LL HANDLE IT.

13:20.987 --> 13:22.823
YOU ALWAYS SAY THAT.

13:22.823 --> 13:24.758
SO DO YOU.

13:24.758 --> 13:25.792
YES.

13:25.792 --> 13:29.530
SOMEHOW THINGS
ALWAYS GET HANDLED.

13:29.530 --> 13:30.831
SOMEHOW THEY DO.

13:30.831 --> 13:31.765
YES.

13:31.765 --> 13:33.667
SO HOW COME
YOU'RE SO EARLY?

13:33.667 --> 13:36.603
I WANTED TO GET A JUMP
ON SOME WORK.

13:36.603 --> 13:38.672
I WAS HOPING IT WAS GOOD NEWS
ABOUT THE CAR, DAVID.

13:38.672 --> 13:39.640
WHAT DID YOUR WIFE SAY?

13:39.640 --> 13:42.275
SHE'S NOT GIVING IT UP.

13:42.275 --> 13:44.044
[ CHUCKLES ]
I SWEAR, I DON'T KNOW WHY

13:44.044 --> 13:46.312
YOU CAN'T GET A BETTER HANDLE
ON THAT WIFE OF YOURS.

13:46.312 --> 13:47.781
SHE'S NOT AN ANIMAL, JIM.
NO, BUT SHE CAN

13:47.781 --> 13:49.716
SURE AS HELL AS ACT LIKE ‐‐
DON'T YOU DARE.

13:49.716 --> 13:51.084
I WILL JUMP ACROSS THIS DESK.

13:51.084 --> 13:53.453
DAVID, I LOVE AND RESPECT
HOW YOU LOVE YOUR WIFE,

13:53.453 --> 13:55.522
BUT THAT WOMAN
IS SOME PIECE OF WORK.

13:55.522 --> 13:57.658
DON'T TALK ABOUT MY WIFE, JIM.

13:57.658 --> 13:59.459
I DON'T TALK ABOUT YOURS.

13:59.459 --> 14:02.068
YOU HAVE PERMISSION
TO TALK ABOUT MY BALL AND CHAIN

14:02.068 --> 14:03.369
ANYTIME YOU WANT.

14:03.369 --> 14:06.006
HOW ARE WE GONNA GET THE CAR
AWAY FROM YOUR BALL AND CHAIN?

14:06.006 --> 14:07.574
I'M WORKING ON IT.

14:07.574 --> 14:09.610
WHAT DOES THAT EVEN MEAN?

14:09.610 --> 14:10.811
I MOVED OUT.

14:12.846 --> 14:14.881
YOU WHAT?

14:14.881 --> 14:18.685
WE HAD A FIGHT ABOUT THE CAR,
AND I LEFT.

14:18.685 --> 14:20.687
THAT'S CERTAINLY A NEW TACT.

14:20.687 --> 14:21.655
YES, IT IS.

14:21.655 --> 14:22.989
THINK IT'LL WORK?

14:22.989 --> 14:25.792
I HOPE SO.

14:25.792 --> 14:28.695
VERONICA
DOESN'T LIKE TO BE ALONE.

14:28.695 --> 14:31.397
HOW LONG DO YOU THINK
IT'LL TAKE?

14:31.397 --> 14:33.534
I DON'T KNOW.

14:35.569 --> 14:37.604
HUH.

14:37.604 --> 14:40.574
IN THE MEANTIME,
WHERE ARE YOU STAYING?

14:40.574 --> 14:42.042
AT THE SARANDON.

14:42.042 --> 14:42.976
THE SARANDON?

14:42.976 --> 14:44.545
[ CHUCKLES ]
I KNOW IT WELL.

14:44.545 --> 14:45.712
OH, I'M SURE YOU DO.

14:45.712 --> 14:47.514
TAKE A LOOK ‐‐
THE LATEST POLL.

14:47.514 --> 14:49.215
NOW,
IT'S NOT SO SCIENTIFIC,

14:49.215 --> 14:50.817
BUT THE PUBLIC FELL FOR IT.

14:50.817 --> 14:52.052
THEY LOVED YOU.

14:52.052 --> 14:54.555
I WAS LOOKING ONLINE
AND READING THE NEWSPAPERS

14:54.555 --> 14:55.689
THIS MORNING.

14:55.689 --> 14:58.224
[ CHUCKLES ]
MY FAVORITE ONLINE QUOTE,

14:58.224 --> 15:01.334
"I WISH JIM CRYER
WERE THE FATHER OF MY CHILDREN.

15:01.334 --> 15:02.903
HE HAS MY VOTE ANY DAY."

15:02.903 --> 15:05.972
SO, LOOKS LIKE WE'RE IN.

15:05.972 --> 15:07.874
UH, I SET UP A PRESS CONFERENCE
FOR THREE DAYS FROM NOW.

15:07.874 --> 15:10.443
WE SHOULD EXPECT GREAT PLACEMENT
AND PLENTY OF HITS.

15:10.443 --> 15:11.377
ACTUALLY, LANDON,

15:11.377 --> 15:12.646
MAKE SURE YOU SET UP
AS MUCH

15:12.646 --> 15:14.247
NATIONAL PRESS COVERAGE
AS YOU CAN.

15:14.247 --> 15:16.016
THAT WILL BE EASY,
SEEING AS HOW EVERYONE

15:16.016 --> 15:17.083
WANTS TO TALK TO YOU NOW.

15:17.083 --> 15:20.621
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

15:20.621 --> 15:22.556
JIM, YOU DON'T SEEM
VERY EXCITED ABOUT THIS.

15:22.556 --> 15:24.525
I AM.
I'M VERY EXCITED.

15:24.525 --> 15:26.860
BUT, UH,
I HAVE TO TAKE THIS.

15:26.860 --> 15:27.728
GOOD JOB.

15:27.728 --> 15:31.397
WHAT IS WRONG WITH HIM?

15:31.397 --> 15:34.467
IT'S, UH...
FAMILY CONCERNS.

15:36.503 --> 15:38.471
HOW'S YOUR FAMILY?

15:40.507 --> 15:42.743
IT'S FINE.

15:42.743 --> 15:44.945
EXCUSE ME.

15:44.945 --> 15:48.114
SURE.

15:53.419 --> 15:54.254
WHAT?

15:54.254 --> 15:55.355
ROSE: We got him.

15:55.355 --> 15:57.658
IT WASN'T TOO HARD TO FIND.

15:57.658 --> 15:59.125
Thank you, Rose.

15:59.125 --> 16:00.934
HOW DO YOU WANT HIM?

16:00.934 --> 16:01.902
ALIVE.

16:01.902 --> 16:03.837
You're taking away
all my fun.

16:03.837 --> 16:07.373
I KEPT YOU OUT OF JAIL.
THAT OUGHT TO BE FUN ENOUGH.

16:07.373 --> 16:08.474
YES, IT IS.

16:08.474 --> 16:10.977
HEY, WHEN ARE YOU COMING
BY THE RESTAURANT?

16:10.977 --> 16:13.947
YOU KNOW I'M RUNNING
FOR GOVERNOR, ROSE.

16:13.947 --> 16:15.215
I CAN'T DO THAT.

16:15.215 --> 16:16.583
I KNOW.

16:16.583 --> 16:20.120
SO, WHERE DO YOU WANT HIM?

16:20.120 --> 16:22.689
MEET ME AT MACK AND 3rd
AT 4:00 P. M. TOMORROW.

16:22.689 --> 16:23.757
Okay.

16:23.757 --> 16:24.858
MM.

16:24.858 --> 16:28.929
OH, HEY,
THIS GIRL IS GETTING RESTLESS.

16:28.929 --> 16:29.796
Good.

16:29.796 --> 16:31.832
LET HER.

16:31.832 --> 16:33.900
SHE'S REALLY SCARED.

16:33.900 --> 16:36.770
IS THAT A FACT?

16:36.770 --> 16:38.204
Yeah.

16:38.204 --> 16:41.508
KEEP HER THAT WAY.

16:41.508 --> 16:43.710
[ BEEP ]

16:43.710 --> 16:45.178
[ GRUNTS ]

16:54.988 --> 16:56.489
ALL RIGHT, NOW,
IF YOU START FEELING

16:56.489 --> 16:59.225
A LITTLE LIGHT‐HEADED,
JUST KEEP HOLDING ON TO ME.

16:59.225 --> 17:00.967
I'M FINE.

17:00.967 --> 17:03.169
THERE YOU GO.

17:03.169 --> 17:05.839
MM.

17:05.839 --> 17:07.508
MM.

17:07.508 --> 17:09.743
HOW ARE YOU FEELING NOW?

17:09.743 --> 17:12.245
[ GRUNTS ]
YOU TELL ME.

17:12.245 --> 17:15.916
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT DOESN'T WORK THAT WAY.

17:17.951 --> 17:20.020
THERE YOU GO.
THERE YOU GO.

17:20.020 --> 17:22.222
I'M FINE, MAN.

17:22.222 --> 17:25.425
YOU STILL FEELING OKAY?

17:25.425 --> 17:27.761
YEAH, I'M FINE.

17:27.761 --> 17:30.531
GOOD. THAT'S GREAT.

17:30.531 --> 17:31.831
YOU'RE DOING WONDERFUL.

17:35.075 --> 17:39.973
NOW I'D LIKE YOU TO TRY IT
ON YOUR OWN, OKAY?

17:39.973 --> 17:42.442
YOU FEEL LIGHT‐HEADED?

17:42.442 --> 17:45.912
MM, NO, MAN,
JUST A HEADACHE.

17:45.912 --> 17:48.048
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

17:48.048 --> 17:50.751
YOU'RE DOING REALLY GOOD.

17:50.751 --> 17:51.785
HOW'S IT FEEL?

17:51.785 --> 17:54.120
I'M TELLING YOU, MAN,
I FEEL FINE.

17:54.120 --> 17:56.489
THIS IS A NICE HOSPITAL,

17:56.489 --> 17:57.858
A LITTLE TOO NICE FOR US.

17:57.858 --> 17:59.660
I NEED TO GET OUT OF HERE,
ALL RIGHT?

17:59.660 --> 18:00.761
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:00.761 --> 18:03.103
I AIN'T GOT
NO HEALTH INSURANCE, SO...

18:03.103 --> 18:04.170
BENNY.

18:04.170 --> 18:08.041
AH, WELL,
YOU KNOW WE CAN'T AFFORD THIS.

18:08.041 --> 18:10.243
IT'S ALL RIGHT, BENNY.

18:10.243 --> 18:11.444
[ SIGHS ]

18:11.444 --> 18:13.747
IS MY TRUCK ALL RIGHT?

18:13.747 --> 18:16.517
BOY, YOU STOP WORRYING
ABOUT THAT TRUCK.

18:16.517 --> 18:18.519
WHERE IS IT AT?

18:18.519 --> 18:19.920
THE POLICE HAVE IT.

18:19.920 --> 18:23.356
WE NEED TO GET IT
'CAUSE I WANT TO GO HOME.

18:23.356 --> 18:25.125
HEY, YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH
A ROUGH ORDEAL.

18:25.125 --> 18:27.493
WE NEED TO RUN SOME MORE TESTS
TO MAKE SURE YOU'RE OKAY.

18:27.493 --> 18:30.296
OKAY.

18:30.296 --> 18:33.667
THEN CAN I GO HOME?

18:33.667 --> 18:36.269
IF EVERYTHING CHECKS OUT,
SURE.

18:36.269 --> 18:37.838
YES.

18:37.838 --> 18:39.439
OOH.

18:39.439 --> 18:40.807
[ GRUNTS ]

18:40.807 --> 18:41.742
COOL.

18:41.742 --> 18:42.676
[ GRUNTS ]

18:42.676 --> 18:44.711
I GOT TO GO TO THE BATHROOM.

18:44.711 --> 18:45.712
IT'S OVER HERE?

18:45.712 --> 18:46.880
THAT'S IT.

18:46.880 --> 18:47.881
COME ON.

18:47.881 --> 18:49.516
BY MYSELF.

18:49.516 --> 18:51.518
OH, BOY,
I CHANGED YOUR DIAPERS.

18:51.518 --> 18:54.387
WELL,
I DONE CHANGED SINCE THEN.

18:54.387 --> 18:56.022
OKAY, THEN, GO ON.

18:56.022 --> 19:00.160
I HOPE EVERYTHING
COMES OUT ALL RIGHT.

19:00.160 --> 19:02.368
THIS IS SHOCKING.

19:02.368 --> 19:04.905
WHAT IS?

19:04.905 --> 19:08.408
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.
THIS DOESN'T HAPPEN.

19:08.408 --> 19:11.277
AND YOU ARE SUCH
A LUCKY PERSON.

19:11.277 --> 19:15.015
NO.
WE ARE VERY BLESSED.

19:15.015 --> 19:18.218
YES, YOU ARE.
YOU ARE BLESSED.

19:18.218 --> 19:22.055
MM.

19:47.514 --> 19:51.351
HEY, WHAT'S UP?

19:51.351 --> 19:52.886
HI.

19:52.886 --> 19:54.721
YOU LIVE HERE?

19:54.721 --> 19:56.590
YEAH.

19:56.590 --> 19:58.358
YOU KNOW A GIRL
NAMED CANDACE?

19:58.358 --> 20:00.734
YEAH, SHE'S MY ROOMMATE.

20:00.734 --> 20:02.068
SHE HERE?

20:02.068 --> 20:03.537
NO.

20:03.537 --> 20:05.171
YOU KNOW
WHEN SHE'LL BE BACK?

20:05.171 --> 20:08.675
UM, I HAVEN'T SEEN HER
IN A COUPLE OF DAYS.

20:08.675 --> 20:09.810
WHO ARE YOU?

20:09.810 --> 20:11.444
MY BAD, SWEETIE.

20:11.444 --> 20:13.146
MY NAME'S QUINCY.

20:13.146 --> 20:15.882
DOES SHE KNOW YOU?

20:15.882 --> 20:17.283
PRETTY WELL.

20:17.283 --> 20:19.520
I'M HER BABY'S FATHER.

20:19.520 --> 20:22.623
YOU MUST HAVE
THE WRONG CANDACE.

20:22.623 --> 20:24.991
SHE DOESN'T HAVE ANY KIDS.

20:24.991 --> 20:26.760
YOU SURE?

20:26.760 --> 20:29.395
YES, THIS CANDACE
IS IN LAW SCHOOL.

20:29.395 --> 20:32.232
IS THIS HER?

20:32.232 --> 20:33.867
YEAH.

20:33.867 --> 20:35.536
OKAY.

20:35.536 --> 20:37.437
WHO'S THE KID?

20:37.437 --> 20:39.506
MY SON.

20:39.506 --> 20:41.007
WHAT?

20:41.007 --> 20:42.843
YEAH.

20:42.843 --> 20:45.912
SHE NEVER MENTIONED A SON.

20:45.912 --> 20:48.114
WELL, SHE HAS ONE.

20:48.114 --> 20:48.949
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:48.949 --> 20:50.617
SHE'S BEEN HOLDING OUT ON ME.

20:50.617 --> 20:53.219
YEAH, I GUESS.

20:53.219 --> 20:55.689
DO YOU WANT TO COME UP?

20:55.689 --> 20:57.691
SURE.

21:14.314 --> 21:16.316
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

21:16.316 --> 21:18.819
THIS IS NICE.

21:18.819 --> 21:20.220
YEAH.

21:20.220 --> 21:21.922
WE DECORATED IT TOGETHER.

21:21.922 --> 21:25.458
WHERE IS SHE?

21:25.458 --> 21:28.394
I'VE BEEN CALLING HER
ALL DAY,

21:28.394 --> 21:31.397
BUT I'LL TRY
CALLING HER AGAIN.

21:31.397 --> 21:32.332
PLEASE.

21:32.332 --> 21:35.836
CAN YOU WRITE HER NUMBER
DOWN FOR ME?

21:35.836 --> 21:39.239
WHY DON'T YOU HAVE
HER NUMBER?

21:39.239 --> 21:41.474
BEEN AWAY.
I LOST TOUCH.

21:41.474 --> 21:42.308
OH.

21:42.308 --> 21:43.644
YOU KNOW HOW THAT GO.

21:43.644 --> 21:45.345
OKAY.

21:45.345 --> 21:47.147
YEAH, I'LL WRITE IT DOWN
FOR YOU.

21:47.147 --> 21:49.182
THANKS.

21:49.182 --> 21:53.319
I CAN'T BELIEVE SHE HAS A KID
AND SHE DIDN'T TELL ME.

21:53.319 --> 21:55.822
WHERE'S THE BABY?

21:55.822 --> 21:58.491
I THINK HE'S WITH HER MOTHER.

21:58.491 --> 22:02.435
OH, OKAY.

22:02.435 --> 22:05.672
WAIT, HER MOTHER DIED.

22:05.672 --> 22:07.541
WHAT?

22:07.541 --> 22:11.277
YEAH, SHE WAS MURDERED
BY HER FATHER.

22:11.277 --> 22:13.346
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

22:13.346 --> 22:16.216
OH, I GET IT.

22:16.216 --> 22:18.451
GET WHAT?

22:18.451 --> 22:19.653
YOU COULDN'T FIND HER

22:19.653 --> 22:21.855
BECAUSE SHE WAS
IN WITNESS PROTECTION.

22:21.855 --> 22:24.324
WITNESS PROTECTION?

22:24.324 --> 22:26.960
YEAH.
SHE WITNESSED THE MURDER.

22:26.960 --> 22:28.662
YOU DIDN'T KNOW THAT?

22:28.662 --> 22:30.496
OH, YEAH.

22:30.496 --> 22:33.667
IT ALL MAKES SENSE.

22:33.667 --> 22:35.468
YEAH.

22:35.468 --> 22:37.170
THAT'S WHY
I COULDN'T REACH HER.

22:46.580 --> 22:49.149
SHE NEVER TALKED
ABOUT YOU.

22:49.149 --> 22:50.651
THAT'S STRANGE,

22:50.651 --> 22:54.087
BECAUSE I TALKED ABOUT HER
EVERY DAY.

22:54.087 --> 22:56.256
OH.

22:56.256 --> 23:00.193
SHE'S NOT ANSWERING
HER CELL.

23:00.193 --> 23:01.301
WOW.

23:01.301 --> 23:02.503
OKAY.

23:02.503 --> 23:04.671
HER VOICEMAIL'S FULL.

23:04.671 --> 23:07.674
SO, YOU DON'T KNOW
WHEN SHE'LL BE BACK?

23:07.674 --> 23:11.444
NO, SORRY.

23:11.444 --> 23:14.581
YOU MIND IF I HANG OUT HERE
FOR A WHILE?

23:14.581 --> 23:16.850
UH, WELL...

23:16.850 --> 23:19.419
I DON'T KNOW.

23:19.419 --> 23:20.721
I'M QUIET.

23:20.721 --> 23:23.624
SURE.

23:23.624 --> 23:24.457
THANKS.

23:24.457 --> 23:26.627
IS THIS HER ROOM OVER HERE?

23:26.627 --> 23:28.461
YEAH.

23:28.461 --> 23:30.196
SHE ALWAYS LIKED PURPLE.

23:30.196 --> 23:31.898
OH, YEAH?

23:31.898 --> 23:33.199
YEAH.

23:33.199 --> 23:37.203
I'M GONNA MAKE SOME DINNER.
DO YOU WANT SOME?

23:37.203 --> 23:39.439
FOR SURE.

23:39.439 --> 23:42.475
ACTUALLY,
I'D LIKE TO HELP YOU COOK.

23:42.475 --> 23:44.110
CAN YOU COOK?

23:44.110 --> 23:46.947
CAN I COOK?
OF COURSE.

23:46.947 --> 23:49.916
I'VE BEEN DOING A LOT OF THAT
THE PAST FEW YEARS.

23:49.916 --> 23:50.917
OKAY, GREAT.

23:50.917 --> 23:53.587
THEN YOU CAN TELL ME
HOW YOU MET HER.

23:53.587 --> 23:55.622
YEAH.

23:55.622 --> 23:57.891
UM, WOULD YOU LIKE
SOME WINE?

23:57.891 --> 24:00.393
SURE.

24:00.393 --> 24:02.068
YOU SMOKE WEED?

24:02.068 --> 24:04.905
UGH, NO.

24:04.905 --> 24:07.874
CAN YOU HELP ME
GET THAT?

24:07.874 --> 24:09.409
YEAH.

24:51.985 --> 24:52.953
CELINE?

24:52.953 --> 24:53.887
YES?

24:53.887 --> 24:56.657
IS WYATT
STILL ON THE LANAI?

24:56.657 --> 24:58.024
NO, HE LEFT.

24:58.024 --> 24:59.092
WHAT?

24:59.092 --> 25:00.366
MM‐HMM.

25:00.366 --> 25:01.334
HOW?

25:01.334 --> 25:02.969
IN YOUR CAR.

25:02.969 --> 25:04.871
GOD.

25:13.013 --> 25:16.683
WYATT?

25:16.683 --> 25:19.252
WYATT!

25:19.252 --> 25:22.288
DAMN IT!

25:23.924 --> 25:25.425
[ Ringing ]

25:25.425 --> 25:26.660
JIM: What is it?

25:26.660 --> 25:27.594
WYATT LEFT.

25:27.594 --> 25:29.429
What?
Where did he go?

25:29.429 --> 25:30.496
I DON'T KNOW.

25:30.496 --> 25:31.532
Damn it, Katheryn,

25:31.532 --> 25:33.567
I specifically told you
to watch him.

25:33.567 --> 25:36.169
You get your ass out there,
and you find him now.

25:36.169 --> 25:38.104
IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

25:38.104 --> 25:42.576
HAVE THE DRIVER
MEET ME AROUND FRONT.

25:42.576 --> 25:43.977
YES, MA'AM.

26:26.960 --> 26:28.962
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M SO SORRY.

26:32.432 --> 26:34.768
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

26:34.768 --> 26:38.404
Tina:
PEOPLE HAVE BEEN COMING ALL DAY.

26:42.809 --> 26:44.645
IT'S JUST SO SAD.

26:44.645 --> 26:47.748
[ Voice breaking ]
YES, IT IS.

26:47.748 --> 26:51.017
SHE WAS SO FULL OF LIFE,

26:51.017 --> 26:53.554
SO ‐‐ SO FUNNY.

26:55.589 --> 26:58.224
YOU KNOW HER?

27:00.260 --> 27:03.504
I'M ‐‐ I'M HER MOTHER.
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:13.279 --> 27:14.881
COME ON, TINA.

27:14.881 --> 27:18.552
NO, I WANT TO STAY
A LITTLE LONGER.

27:18.552 --> 27:20.353
I KNOW.

27:20.353 --> 27:22.355
COME ON.

27:24.825 --> 27:27.360
IT WAS YOU.

27:29.395 --> 27:31.231
EXCUSE ME?

27:31.231 --> 27:32.132
YOU.

27:32.132 --> 27:34.367
DON'T I KNOW YOU?

27:34.367 --> 27:36.002
YOU DID IT.

27:36.002 --> 27:37.037
IT WAS YOU!

27:37.037 --> 27:38.204
DAD, THAT'S HIM.
THAT'S THE GUY THAT ‐‐

27:38.204 --> 27:39.039
HEY!

27:39.039 --> 27:41.207
HEY!

27:43.143 --> 27:44.210
IT WAS YOU!

27:44.210 --> 27:45.546
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

27:45.546 --> 27:47.213
[ YELLS INDISTINCTLY ]

27:47.213 --> 27:49.182
AND I KNOW IT WAS YOU!

27:49.182 --> 27:50.183
STOP!

27:50.183 --> 27:54.287
[ SOBS ]

27:54.287 --> 27:55.756
OH!

28:08.441 --> 28:09.676
[ SNIFFLES ]

28:09.676 --> 28:10.977
THAT WAS HIM.

28:10.977 --> 28:12.946
[ BOTH SOBBING ]

28:21.622 --> 28:23.356
UH, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

28:23.356 --> 28:25.926
I'M GETTING READY FOR BED.
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:25.926 --> 28:27.027
YOU GOING HOME.

28:27.027 --> 28:27.961
NO, I'M NOT.

28:27.961 --> 28:28.929
YES, YOU ARE.

28:28.929 --> 28:30.430
BENNY.

28:30.430 --> 28:32.465
MOMMY, GO HOME.
I'M FINE.

28:32.465 --> 28:34.200
LOOK AT ME.
COME ON.

28:34.200 --> 28:35.335
I'M NOT LEAVING YOU.

28:35.335 --> 28:36.402
[ LAUGHS ]

28:36.402 --> 28:38.071
WHEN THE LAST TIME
YOU ATE SOMETHING?

28:38.071 --> 28:39.472
I ATE.

28:39.472 --> 28:41.107
GO HOME.

28:41.107 --> 28:42.442
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

28:42.442 --> 28:43.276
HEY.

28:43.276 --> 28:44.110
HEY.

28:44.110 --> 28:45.145
GO HOME.

28:45.145 --> 28:46.647
UH, ANY TRASH?

28:46.647 --> 28:50.116
AH, I SEE.

28:50.116 --> 28:52.786
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

28:52.786 --> 28:54.521
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:54.521 --> 28:58.258
NO, HONEY,
THERE'S NO TRASH.

28:58.258 --> 29:00.293
I'M GOING HOME.

29:00.293 --> 29:02.335
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.

29:02.335 --> 29:03.236
SEE YA.

29:03.236 --> 29:04.337
MWAH!

29:04.337 --> 29:06.239
I LOVE YOU VERY MUCH, SON.

29:06.239 --> 29:08.141
[ SMOOCHES ]
I LOVE YOU.

29:08.141 --> 29:09.175
BE CAREFUL.

29:09.175 --> 29:11.477
[ LAUGHS ]
BYE, MS. HANNA.

29:11.477 --> 29:12.345
BYE.

29:14.314 --> 29:17.784
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

29:17.784 --> 29:19.419
HOW YOU DOING?

29:19.419 --> 29:20.854
YOU WERE SINGING TO ME.

29:20.854 --> 29:24.591
[ CHUCKLES ]
UH, WHO, ME?

29:24.591 --> 29:26.359
UH, YEAH.

29:26.359 --> 29:27.528
NO, I WASN'T.

29:27.528 --> 29:29.763
[ LAUGHS ]
YES, YOU WERE.

29:29.763 --> 29:31.665
YEAH, I WAS.

29:31.665 --> 29:32.999
MM‐HMM.

29:32.999 --> 29:34.535
YOU HEARD ME?

29:34.535 --> 29:35.368
YEAH.

29:35.368 --> 29:36.603
[ LAUGHS ]

29:36.603 --> 29:37.871
THANK YOU.

29:37.871 --> 29:40.607
YOU'RE WELCOME.

29:40.607 --> 29:43.644
SO, WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

29:43.644 --> 29:47.080
DARLENE.

29:49.115 --> 29:50.483
DARLENE.

29:50.483 --> 29:51.785
MM‐HMM.

29:56.089 --> 29:57.824
DARLENE FROM HIGH SCHOOL.

29:57.824 --> 29:58.725
YEAH.

29:58.725 --> 30:00.767
[ Laughing ] WHAT?

30:00.767 --> 30:01.702
YO.

30:01.702 --> 30:04.605
DAMN, YOU LOOK GOOD.

30:04.605 --> 30:05.939
WELL, THANK YOU.

30:05.939 --> 30:06.740
MM‐HMM.

30:06.740 --> 30:07.941
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

30:07.941 --> 30:08.975
YOU KNOW...

30:08.975 --> 30:10.644
I USED TO, UM...

30:10.644 --> 30:14.014
YOU USED TO BE REALLY NICE
TO ME.

30:14.014 --> 30:15.516
OH, YEAH?

30:15.516 --> 30:17.651
YEAH, YOU WERE.

30:17.651 --> 30:19.886
MM. [ CHUCKLES ]

30:19.886 --> 30:21.121
YOU WANT TO, UH...

30:21.121 --> 30:23.857
YOU WANT TO STAY AND TALK
WITH ME FOR A WHILE?

30:23.857 --> 30:27.293
I WOULD,
BUT, UH, I HAVE TO WORK.

30:27.293 --> 30:29.963
WHAT ABOUT AFTER WORK?

30:29.963 --> 30:32.799
I'LL BE BACK IN A FEW HOURS.

30:32.799 --> 30:34.568
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

30:34.568 --> 30:36.102
I'LL BE HERE.

30:36.102 --> 30:36.970
OKAY.

30:36.970 --> 30:37.804
OKAY.

30:37.804 --> 30:39.540
IT WAS NICE TO SEE YOU.

30:39.540 --> 30:42.008
YOU, TOO.

30:42.008 --> 30:45.211
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

30:45.211 --> 30:47.648
HEY, GIRL!

30:55.822 --> 30:57.090
HEY.

30:57.090 --> 30:58.391
HEY.

30:58.391 --> 31:00.801
HOW ARE YOU?

31:00.801 --> 31:02.869
MY DAUGHTER SAW HIM.

31:02.869 --> 31:04.404
SAW WHO?

31:04.404 --> 31:05.539
THE MAN WHO DID IT.

31:05.539 --> 31:07.841
IT WAS THE ONE
THEY ARRESTED AND LET GO.

31:07.841 --> 31:10.376
I THINK THEY'RE LYING,
MICHAEL.

31:10.376 --> 31:14.314
THOSE PEOPLE WILL DO ANYTHING
TO PROTECT THEIR CHILD.

31:14.314 --> 31:16.049
YEAH, MAN.

31:16.049 --> 31:17.884
COME ON IN.

31:17.884 --> 31:19.920
LISTEN, I GOT A FRIEND
WHO IS A DETECTIVE.

31:19.920 --> 31:21.822
HIS NAME IS BYRON,
AND WE'LL CALL HIM.

31:21.822 --> 31:23.423
AND HE'LL LOOK
INTO THIS, OKAY?

31:23.423 --> 31:24.390
ALL RIGHT.

31:24.390 --> 31:25.291
COME ON.

31:44.845 --> 31:46.847
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:49.650 --> 31:50.984
DAVID!

31:57.357 --> 31:58.525
HI.

31:58.525 --> 31:59.993
RESCUE ME.

31:59.993 --> 32:01.835
PARDON?

32:01.835 --> 32:04.871
YOU SEE THAT OLD MAN
AT THE END OF THE BAR?

32:04.871 --> 32:06.507
YES.

32:06.507 --> 32:08.274
[ CHUCKLES ] HELP.

32:08.274 --> 32:10.911
[ LAUGHS ]

32:10.911 --> 32:15.348
YEAH, I SUPPOSE
I CAN SIT FOR A MOMENT.

32:15.348 --> 32:16.917
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:16.917 --> 32:18.351
THANK YOU.

32:18.351 --> 32:19.953
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:19.953 --> 32:21.688
YOU KNOW THE PRESS CONFERENCE

32:21.688 --> 32:24.090
IS GONNA BE HUGE
FOR THE ANNOUNCEMENT.

32:24.090 --> 32:25.759
IS IT?
OH, YEAH, ABSOLUTELY.

32:25.759 --> 32:27.728
I NEVER GET
THIS KIND OF RESPONSE.

32:27.728 --> 32:28.795
OH, THAT'S GREAT.

32:28.795 --> 32:29.596
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:29.596 --> 32:33.099
YEAH.

32:33.099 --> 32:36.136
HOW MUCH HAVE YOU HAD?

32:36.136 --> 32:37.403
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:37.403 --> 32:40.541
NOT ENOUGH TO DEAL
WITH JIM CRYER.

32:40.541 --> 32:41.642
MY FRIEND.

32:41.642 --> 32:43.276
YOU WANT A DRINK?

32:43.276 --> 32:45.145
OH, RIGHT, I'M SORRY.

32:45.145 --> 32:46.880
YOU ‐‐ YOU DON'T DRINK.

32:46.880 --> 32:49.382
IS ‐‐ IS THIS A PROBLEM
FOR YOU?

32:49.382 --> 32:51.184
NO, NO.

32:53.219 --> 32:55.488
VERONICA HAD A PROBLEM,

32:55.488 --> 32:58.659
SO I DON'T DRINK
FOR HER SAKE,

32:58.659 --> 33:01.635
BUT, UM...

33:01.635 --> 33:04.104
BUT TONIGHT, I WILL.

33:04.104 --> 33:06.973
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

33:06.973 --> 33:11.945
UH, I'LL HAVE A SCOTCH,
NEAT.

33:11.945 --> 33:13.914
THANK YOU.

33:13.914 --> 33:16.650
THAT'S NOBLE.

33:16.650 --> 33:18.619
WHAT'S THAT?

33:18.619 --> 33:21.688
YOU REALLY LOVE HER.

33:21.688 --> 33:24.157
YES, I DO.

33:26.793 --> 33:29.663
HOW'S YOUR BED HERE?

33:34.300 --> 33:35.636
UH...

33:35.636 --> 33:37.604
IT'S FINE.

33:37.604 --> 33:38.438
OH.

33:38.438 --> 33:40.173
MINE WAS TOO HARD.

33:40.173 --> 33:43.510
SO, I, UM ‐‐
I MOVED ROOMS TO 1128.

33:43.510 --> 33:45.612
HUH, I'M IN 1129.

33:45.612 --> 33:48.214
1129.
YEAH, I KNOW.

33:48.214 --> 33:51.384
[ CHUCKLES ]
THEY ADJOIN.

33:51.384 --> 33:52.919
OH.

34:00.727 --> 34:04.505
WELL, I HOPE YOUR BED
IS BETTER.

34:04.505 --> 34:06.239
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:06.239 --> 34:10.844
IT WOULD BE
IF I WASN'T ALONE IN IT.

34:10.844 --> 34:14.014
WELL, THERE'S A MAN.

34:14.014 --> 34:16.282
HE'S RIGHT OVER THERE.

34:16.282 --> 34:18.184
[ Laughing ] STOP.

34:18.184 --> 34:21.855
EVEN A 30‐SOMETHING
WHO'S NEVER BEEN MARRIED

34:21.855 --> 34:25.158
HAS STANDARDS, DAVID.

34:30.864 --> 34:33.900
HAVE YOU EVER HAD AN AFFAIR?

34:33.900 --> 34:35.301
NO.

34:35.301 --> 34:37.538
COME ON.

34:37.538 --> 34:38.939
NO.

34:38.939 --> 34:42.108
YOU EVER THOUGHT ABOUT IT?

34:42.108 --> 34:43.343
MAGGIE,

34:43.343 --> 34:44.711
I LOVE MY WIFE.

34:44.711 --> 34:45.712
[ SCOFFS ]

34:45.712 --> 34:48.281
OF COURSE,
YOU'VE THOUGHT ABOUT IT.

34:51.852 --> 34:53.720
WELL, DAVID,
IF YOU EVER DO ‐‐

34:53.720 --> 34:55.455
I WON'T.

34:55.455 --> 34:59.059
IF YOU EVER DO...

35:02.035 --> 35:03.970
DON'T DO WHAT JIM DID.

35:03.970 --> 35:07.307
DON'T GET A WHORE
FROM SOME ONLINE AD.

35:07.307 --> 35:09.643
YOU SEE HOW THAT TURNED OUT.

35:09.643 --> 35:11.111
YES, I DO.

35:13.714 --> 35:15.448
YOU SHOULD SLEEP
WITH SOMEONE

35:15.448 --> 35:17.417
WHO HAS AS MUCH TO LOSE
AS YOU DO.

35:21.454 --> 35:23.924
SOMEBODY, UM...

35:25.959 --> 35:29.295
SOMEBODY LIKE MICHELLE OBAMA.

35:29.295 --> 35:32.398
[ LAUGHS ]

35:32.398 --> 35:34.868
MM. MM.

35:34.868 --> 35:38.805
OR MAGGIE DAY?

35:38.805 --> 35:42.576
YEAH, WELL...

35:42.576 --> 35:45.111
IT'S GETTING LATE.

35:45.111 --> 35:46.547
YEAH.

35:46.547 --> 35:49.516
I SAID TOO MUCH.

35:49.516 --> 35:50.383
NO.

35:50.383 --> 35:51.718
DRANK TOO MUCH.

35:51.718 --> 35:53.119
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:53.119 --> 35:55.622
WOULD YOU WALK ME TO MY ROOM?

35:58.825 --> 36:00.293
1128.

36:00.293 --> 36:01.401
MM‐HMM.

36:01.401 --> 36:04.571
NEXT TO 1129.

36:04.571 --> 36:07.240
[ LAUGHS ]

36:14.414 --> 36:16.382
OKAY.

36:18.351 --> 36:19.720
[ LAUGHS ]

36:27.327 --> 36:29.229
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

36:29.229 --> 36:30.263
[ BEEP ]

36:30.263 --> 36:31.397
GO.

36:31.397 --> 36:35.268
MAN: The mother of the child
identified your son.

36:35.268 --> 36:36.369
WHAT?!

36:36.369 --> 36:39.339
I'm on my way to Hanna's
to take the statement.

36:39.339 --> 36:41.207
WHERE DID SHE SEE HIM?

36:41.207 --> 36:43.476
He went
to the child's gravesite.

36:43.476 --> 36:45.646
AH, DAMN IT, WYATT!

36:45.646 --> 36:50.216
I'LL TAKE CARE OF MY SON.
YOU HANDLE THAT.

36:50.216 --> 36:51.785
Sure.

36:51.785 --> 36:53.820
[ BEEP ]

36:57.257 --> 36:59.693
WHO'S THERE?

37:09.509 --> 37:10.977
JIM.

37:10.977 --> 37:13.713
HELLO, LOVE.

37:13.713 --> 37:16.616
ARE YOU CRAZY,
OR HAVE YOU LOST YOUR MIND?

37:16.616 --> 37:19.720
WELL, THAT DEPENDS ON
WHETHER OR NOT YOU FOUND YOURS.

37:19.720 --> 37:22.923
I WANT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

37:22.923 --> 37:26.026
[ Laughing ]
I'LL BET YOU DO.

37:26.026 --> 37:28.394
DID MY BROTHER
HAVE A FUNERAL?

37:28.394 --> 37:30.931
HOW WOULD I KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT THAT?

37:32.966 --> 37:36.937
LET ME OUT OF HERE.

37:36.937 --> 37:38.905
PLEASE.

37:38.905 --> 37:42.643
WOW, YOU CAN SAY PLEASE.

37:42.643 --> 37:45.011
SAY IT AGAIN.

37:48.048 --> 37:49.616
PLEASE.

37:49.616 --> 37:52.819
HMM.

37:52.819 --> 37:56.623
OKAY, CANDACE,
WHAT ARE THE RULES?

37:56.623 --> 37:57.457
WHAT?

37:57.457 --> 37:58.959
THE RULES, CANDACE.

37:58.959 --> 38:01.735
WE WENT OVER THE RULES.
WHAT ARE THEY?

38:01.735 --> 38:05.138
WHAT DID I ASK YOU FOR?
WHAT DID I ASK YOU TO DO?

38:05.138 --> 38:07.974
ON THE BENCH,
WHAT DID I ASK YOU TO DO?

38:07.974 --> 38:09.342
LEAVE YOUR DAUGHTER ALONE.

38:09.342 --> 38:11.177
LEAVE MY DAUGHTER ALONE,
EXACTLY.

38:11.177 --> 38:12.646
WHAT ELSE
DID I ASK YOU TO DO?

38:12.646 --> 38:15.982
GET RID OF THE BABY.

38:15.982 --> 38:17.818
GET RID OF THE BABY,

38:17.818 --> 38:21.254
BUT THERE WAS NEVER ANY BABY,
WAS THERE, CANDACE?

38:21.254 --> 38:24.024
NO.

38:24.024 --> 38:28.028
NO, NEVER WAS A BABY.

38:28.028 --> 38:30.797
IMAGINE THAT.

38:30.797 --> 38:33.299
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
I WAS GOING TO YOUR APARTMENT.

38:33.299 --> 38:35.769
HOW DID YOU MANAGE TO HAVE
THAT PREGNANCY TEST?

38:35.769 --> 38:36.837
DID YOU STAGE THAT?

38:36.837 --> 38:38.672
YES.

38:38.672 --> 38:42.576
THAT WAS GOOD.

38:42.576 --> 38:44.845
SMART.

38:51.351 --> 38:53.720
SIGN THESE.

38:53.720 --> 38:55.789
WHAT'S THIS?

38:55.789 --> 38:57.924
TAKE THE PEN, CANDACE.

38:59.960 --> 39:01.902
THIS...

39:01.902 --> 39:05.305
IS DROPPING THE LAWSUIT
AGAINST ME AND MY FAMILY

39:05.305 --> 39:07.073
FOR AMANDA'S INHERITANCE.

39:07.073 --> 39:09.275
SIGN IT.

39:11.978 --> 39:13.479
THIS IS AN AFFIDAVIT

39:13.479 --> 39:16.482
STATING
THAT YOU HAVE BEEN STALKING ME

39:16.482 --> 39:18.685
AND THAT YOU'RE NOT ONLY
A DANGER TO YOURSELF,

39:18.685 --> 39:20.821
BUT YOU'RE ALSO A DANGER
TO ME AND MY FAMILY.

39:20.821 --> 39:23.056
FURTHERMORE, IT STATES
THAT YOU ARE DELUSIONAL,

39:23.056 --> 39:25.458
AND YOU HAVE BEEN SUFFERING
FROM FANTASIES ABOUT ME

39:25.458 --> 39:26.359
THAT ARE NOT REAL.

39:26.359 --> 39:27.227
SIGN IT.

39:32.332 --> 39:33.834
THIS...

39:33.834 --> 39:37.504
YEAH.

39:37.504 --> 39:38.605
RESTRAINING ORDER,

39:38.605 --> 39:40.507
SAYING
THAT YOU WILL NEVER COME

39:40.507 --> 39:42.676
ANYWHERE NEAR ME
OR MY FAMILY AGAIN.

39:42.676 --> 39:43.710
SIGN IT.

39:48.849 --> 39:51.051
AND THIS...

39:51.051 --> 39:52.686
IS THE TITLE TO YOUR CAR.

39:52.686 --> 39:56.289
YOU'LL BE SIGNING IT OVER TO ME,
AND I WILL BE SELLING IT.

39:56.289 --> 39:57.323
SIGN IT.

40:10.243 --> 40:12.613
THAT WAS EASY.

40:12.613 --> 40:14.748
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:14.748 --> 40:17.183
I SIGNED IT, NOW WHAT?

40:19.219 --> 40:21.988
YOU'LL NEVER BOTHER ME AGAIN?

40:24.024 --> 40:26.560
NO.

40:26.560 --> 40:28.361
YOU NEED TO PROMISE.

40:28.361 --> 40:31.231
YOU NEED
TO MAKE ME BELIEVE IT.

40:31.231 --> 40:34.000
I'M GONNA ASK YOU
ONE MORE TIME.

40:34.000 --> 40:37.270
YOU ARE NEVER
GOING TO BOTHER ME AGAIN.

40:37.270 --> 40:39.439
I WILL NEVER SEE YOU AGAIN.

40:39.439 --> 40:40.607
YOU PROMISE?

40:40.607 --> 40:43.009
YES.

40:43.009 --> 40:47.013
I PROMISE.

40:50.517 --> 40:54.855
WHAT DO YOU WANT ME TO DO
WITH HER?

41:08.241 --> 41:09.576
KILL HER.

41:09.576 --> 41:11.077
JIM, THESE PEOPLE ‐‐

41:11.077 --> 41:13.446
THESE PEOPLE
WILL DO ANYTHING.

41:13.446 --> 41:16.216
JIM, NO! JIM!

41:18.251 --> 41:20.787
JIM, PLEASE?

41:25.726 --> 41:27.260
JIM...

41:31.464 --> 41:34.000
<i>NEXT ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS."</i>

41:34.000 --> 41:36.169
I KNOW
YOU FIND ME ATTRACTIVE.

41:36.169 --> 41:37.337
LET ME GO NOW.

41:37.337 --> 41:38.739
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU.

41:38.739 --> 41:40.240
IT'S JUST A LITTLE ‐‐

41:40.240 --> 41:42.108
A LITTLE MESSED UP
I FOUND OUT LIKE THAT.

41:42.108 --> 41:43.243
YOUR MOM SAID YOU WERE CUTE.

41:43.243 --> 41:45.979
YOUR MOM WAS SO PERSISTENT
THAT WE MEET.

41:45.979 --> 41:47.313
GET YOUR THINGS,
I'M TAKING YOU HOME.

41:47.313 --> 41:48.348
DAD, I ‐‐

41:48.348 --> 41:49.916
WHERE'S THE GUN?

41:49.916 --> 41:50.817
WHAT GUN?

41:50.817 --> 41:52.252
I WANT TO COME HOME.

41:52.252 --> 41:54.087
DON'T MAKE ME HANG UP
ON YOU, DAVID.

41:54.087 --> 41:55.622
ALL I HAVE TO DO IS COP
TO THE WARRANTS I HAVE.

41:55.622 --> 41:56.823
AND ONE MORE.

41:56.823 --> 41:57.724
ON YOUR KNEES, HONEY.

41:57.724 --> 41:59.593
NO, WAIT. NO.
I PROMISE YOU ‐‐

41:59.593 --> 42:01.434
THEN YOU'LL BE SHOT
IN THE FACE!
